---
import PageHero from "../../components/PageHero.astro";
import SAGPLayout from "../../layouts/SAGPLayout.astro";
---

<SAGPLayout title="Membership | Society for Ancient Greek Philosophy">

<PageHero
  kicker="Membership"
  title="Join a worldwide conversation about Ancient Greek philosophy."
  subtitle="SAGP membership is open to scholars and students of Ancient Greek philosophy and supports the Society’s conferences, lectures, mentoring, and international scholarly community."
  image="/assets/images/delphi_treasury.jpg"
/>

<section class="section two-col">
  <div>
    <h2>Why become a member?</h2>
  </div>

  <div>
    <p>
      Membership connects you to one of the largest scholarly communities
      devoted specifically to Ancient Greek philosophy. SAGP currently maintains
      a mailing list of approximately 1,500 people and continues to grow both
      nationally and internationally.
    </p>

    <p>
      Members support and participate in the Society’s scholarly life, including
      the Annual Conference, Distinguished Lectureship, Works in Progress series,
      and SAGP-sponsored panels at meetings of other associations.
    </p>

    <div class="callout">
      Membership is not simply a transaction. It is an invitation into a
      conversation that has continued since 1953.
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <h2>What membership supports</h2>

  <div class="card-grid">
    <article class="card">
      <h3>Scholarly events</h3>
      <p>
        Membership supports the Annual Conference, Distinguished Lectureship,
        Works in Progress series, and SAGP-sponsored panels.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <h3>International community</h3>
      <p>
        Members help sustain a global community of scholars and students working
        across traditions, institutions, and countries.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <h3>Mentorship and participation</h3>
      <p>
        SAGP especially encourages junior and mid-career scholars to present
        their work and become part of the Society’s scholarly life.
      </p>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section two-col">
  <div>
    <h2>How membership works</h2>
  </div>

  <div>
    <p>
      SAGP annual dues are established and periodically reassessed by the
      President, Secretary, Assistant Secretary, and Board of Directors.
    </p>

    <p>
      Each membership year begins on September 1 and ends on August 31.
      Membership may be paid for one, three, or five years.
    </p>

    <p>
      Current membership is only <strong>$10 per year</strong>. Membership is
      required for attendance at SAGP conferences and events.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section two-col">
  <div>
    <h2>Become a member</h2>
  </div>

  <div>
    <p>
      To become a SAGP member, download the membership form, choose a one-year,
      three-year, or five-year membership, and submit payment either by check or
      by credit card.
    </p>

    <p>
      <a
        href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/documents/SAGP-Membership-Form-2026.docx`}
        download
      >
        Download the SAGP Membership Form →
      </a>
    </p>

    <p>
      If paying by check, print the completed form and mail it with payment to
      the address listed on the form.
    </p>

    <p>
      If paying by credit card, fill out the top part of the form, email it to
      Tony Preus, and use the online payment link.
    </p>

    <p>
      International members may also arrange bank transfers by contacting Tony
      Preus.
    </p>

  </div>
</section>

</SAGPLayout>
